'''Glitnir''' (glit, nitor, splendor, [[Old High German|OHG]]. kliz, E. shining) is the hall of [[Forseti]], the [[Norse mythology|Norse]] god of law and justice, and the seat of justice amongst [[Æsir|gods]] and men. It is also noted to have been a place of dwelling for [[Balder]], Forseti's father in Norse and [[Germanic mythology|Germanic mythologies]]. Glitnir is symbolic of the importance of discussion rather than violence as a means of resolution of conflict within the Norse tradition. It has pillars of [[gold]] and is roofed with [[silver]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.northvegr.org/lore/grimmst/011_03.php |title=Grimm's TM - Chap. 11 |publisher=Northvegr |date= |accessdate=2018-05-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080517073207/http://www.northvegr.org/lore/grimmst/011_03.php |archive-date=2008-05-17 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

